FBIS4-65853 "drweu100_q_94010" FBIS-WEU-94-100 Daily Report 21 May 1994 TURKEY Villagers Attack SDPP Delegation in Erzincan Villagers Attack SDPP Delegation in Erzincan TA2105151594 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1500 GMT 21 May 94 TA2105151594 Ankara ANATOLIA English BFN [Text] Erzincan, May 21 (A.A.) -- Villagers attacked Social Democratic Populist Party [SDPP] Deputy Mustafa Kul and 20 party members in Edebuk village in Tercan township in eastern Erzincan Province it was reported on Saturday [21 May]. Kul, speaking to AA [Anatolia Agency] reporters, said they went to the village to express sorrow for the death of nine civilians after an attack by the outlawed separatist terrorist organization which happened last week. He said: "Nearly 100 people attacked us and our cars with sticks and stones". Kul said the attack could be a reaction of the villagers against the PKK [Workers Party of Kurdistan] attack. Erzincan Governor Recep Yazicioglu said he condemned the attack adding that an investigation has been launched into the incident.
